news.title: Government approval delays six town planning schemes in Pune metropolitan region
news.para: ​​Five of them are planned along the proposed ring road and the sixth one is related to Maan-Mhalunge, which was showcased as a model scheme in the 2019 assembly polls.

news.title: Thane civic body releases draft of revised development plan
news.para: The revised development plan, along with detailed plans and maps, is available for public access on the TMC website and also at the municipal headquarters at Panchpakhadi. Copies of these can be obtained by paying a nominal fee," said a civic official.

news.title: Maharashtra government approves two new metro rail routes for Pune
news.para: The decision to approve construction of the Khadakwasla-Swargate-Hadapsar-Kharadi and Nalstop-Dahanukar Colony-Warje-Manikbaug metro rail routes was taken in the cabinet meeting, an official said.

news.title: Government approves Bengaluru metro phase 3A project
news.para: The budget estimate for this project in 2022-23 was around Rs 16,500 crore, but following the detailed project report, the estimated cost has now risen to Rs 27,000 crore.

news.title: BBMP’s e-khata pilot sees only 8.6% success in Bengaluru's east zone
news.para: Introduced on a pilot basis in 2022, the e-khata initiative aimed to bring transparency and streamline the process of managing property records. However, the uptake has been slower than expected.

news.title: Delhi civic body prepares plan to control dust pollution and illegal dumping of C&D waste
news.para: The civic body has formed 386 surveillance teams, comprising 1,307 officers, to monitor and prevent open burning of garbage and illegal dumping of construction and demolition (C&D) waste.

news.title: Delhi environment minister fines construction company for flouting anti-dust rules
news.para: Speaking to reporters on-site, Rai said, "Despite repeated instructions to follow the anti-dust campaign rules, I found that the necessary measures were not implemented in this construction site. This site being less than 20,000 square metre, it required to strictly comply with the dust-control norms."

news.title: Maharashtra government allows PCNTDA properties’ conversion into freehold
news.para: Now-dissolved Pimpri-Chinchwad New Township Development Authority located in Pune Metropolitan Region Development Authority freehold, which will allow more than 11,000 propery holders to become legal owners

news.title: Gujarat government to seek public input before finalising new jantri rates
news.para: The revenue department is set to release city- and area-specific jantri rates soon. "In 2023, when jantri rates were doubled, it caused a major stir in the real estate sector, leading to the postponement of the new rates.

news.title: Haryana RERA moves HC over 207 arrest warrants issued against 20 builders
news.para: H-Rera officials said police had, however, not acted on the orders, prompting the regulator to move the Punjab and Haryana high court for its intervention. H-Rera has initiated contempt of court proceedings in three such cases against police for their inaction.

news.title: SC notice to Centre on plea against unauthorised constructions on riverbeds, floodplains
news.para: A bench of Chief Justice D Y Chandrachud and Justices J B Pardiwala and Manoj Misra issued notices to the Environment Ministry, Ministry of Jal Shakti, Ministry of Earth Sciences, Central Water Commission and the Central Pollution Control Board while seeking their replies within three weeks.

news.title: Cement industry growth to slow down to 7-8% to 475 MT in FY25: Report
news.para: ​​The cement demand grew only 3 per cent in the June first quarter of FY2024-25, owing to an extended heatwave and shortage of labour during general elections and is estimated to have grown at a similar pace in the second quarter due to seasonal weakness.

news.title: Delhi HC asks CBI to file status report on DHFL ex-director's bail plea
news.para: Justice Chandra Dhari Singh asked the CBI to file within 10 days its status report on various aspects, including its objections raised on the maintainability of the petition.

news.title: Sattva Group partners with Bain Capital to develop co-living platform
news.para: The platform will be housed under Colive, a company that manages rental homes, they said, adding that this is the largest funding received so far by a coliving platform to develop a built-to-suit co-living asset.

news.title: Real estate equity investment reaches $8.9 billion in Jan-Sept 2024: Report
news.para: On a quarterly basis, equity investments in real estate stood at $2.6 billion in Q2 FY25.

news.title: Issued final notifications to enforce fire safety norms for vulnerable buildings: Maharashtra government
news.para: The notification would include security rules in Development Control and Promotion Regulations (DCPR), 2034, for Greater Mumbai and Unified Development Control And Promotion Regulations (UDCPR) for the rest of the state.

news.title: Goa: Residents of Betalbatim oppose mega construction projects
news.para: ​Pointing to a number of people from outside Goa investing in properties in the village, which were later sold at exorbitant prices, villagers asserted that they would not allow their land to be used for mega construction projects.

news.title: Bajaj housing finance shares drop 4% as one month lock-in period expires on October 14
news.para: This means that approximately 12.6 crore (126 million) shares of the company, which were previously locked in and prohibited from sale, will now be eligible to be sold.
